<item>
            <title>[LU-1566]  Suggested Lustre Version</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1566</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;My name is Bob Torgerson, and I work as an HPC Analyst for the Arctic&lt;br/&gt;
Region Supercomputing Center in Fairbanks, Alaska. Recently, we have been&lt;br/&gt;
working to build a Lustre file system for our high performance systems and&lt;br/&gt;
desktop clients, a file system with a total storage capacity of&lt;br/&gt;
approximately 290 TB. We decided to go with Lustre version 1.8.8 for our&lt;br/&gt;
initial install on the suggestion of Zhiqi Tao, my instructor in a&lt;br/&gt;
WhamCloud training in Alexandria, VA. We have moved forward with the&lt;br/&gt;
installation using Lustre 1.8.8  on RHEL 5 servers and have a working file&lt;br/&gt;
system able to be exported to our clients. However, we have had some issues&lt;br/&gt;
related to hardware such as newer QLogic cards being unsupported in RHEL 5&lt;br/&gt;
that appear that they would be resolved by upgrading to RHEL 6, but at this&lt;br/&gt;
point, Lustre 1.8.8 is unsupported on RHEL 6 servers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before we move further forward with our implementation, I would like to&lt;br/&gt;
discuss with WhamCloud support what version of the Lustre software is&lt;br/&gt;
recommended for production. We have the 1.8.8 Lustre file system working&lt;br/&gt;
now, but have not invited beta testers to try it yet, meaning that we still&lt;br/&gt;
have time to make changes including what version of Lustre we use before we&lt;br/&gt;
invite users to use the file system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any suggestions you could provide to me would be greatly appreciated!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you in advance,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Terry &lt;br/&gt;
Penguin Tech Support&lt;br/&gt;
Ph. 415-954-2833&lt;/p&gt;</description>
