                            <comment id="41641" author="cliffw" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 19:36:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41638" author="tsingh" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 18:34:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Cliff, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Yes, I did answer my questions. Please go ahead and close the case. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;br/&gt;
Terry&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41627" author="cliffw" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 16:41:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did this answer your question? Can we do anything more for you on this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41206" author="pjones" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 13:33:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would agree that 2.1.x is a sensible approach but I want to clarify that 1.8.x is &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; due for retirement. We plan to keep supporting it as long as sufficient demand is there, but recognize that this demand will wane over time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41164" author="cliffw" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2012 16:59:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As you wish to run Redhat 6, we would advise you moving to Lustre 2.1, our current production release.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/latest-maintenance-release/el6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/lustre/latest-maintenance-release/el6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will position you for the future, and eliminate the RHEL6 issue. The 1.8 stream is due for retirement (see the Lustre Roadmap &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Community+Lustre+Roadmap&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Community+Lustre+Roadmap&lt;/a&gt;), and especially for a new implementation, we would advise Lustre 2.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
